            <section class="prose">
              <h2>How to convert tonnes to kilograms</h2>
              <p>
                A <strong>tonne</strong> (also called a
                <strong>metric ton</strong> and written as <code>t</code>) is
                defined as exactly <strong>1,000 kilograms</strong>. This makes
                the conversion between tonnes and kilograms very
                straightforward.
              </p>

              <div class="formula-box">
                <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Tonnes to kilograms formula</p>
                <p class="mb-1"><code>kilograms = tonnes × 1,000</code></p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                  Example: <code>2.5 t × 1,000 = 2,500 kg</code>
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="formula-box">
                <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Kilograms to tonnes formula</p>
                <p class="mb-1"><code>tonnes = kilograms ÷ 1,000</code></p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                  Example: <code>7,500 kg ÷ 1,000 = 7.5 t</code>
                </p>
              </div>

